    intro: 'GitOps starts from one rule: the desired state of your system lives in Git, and nothing else. A dedicated config repository holds the declarative manifests that describe exactly what should be running — every Deployment, Service, ConfigMap, and Helm value. This is deliberately separate from your application source code: the app repo builds the image, the config repo declares which image runs where. Git becomes the control plane. Every change to production is a commit, every deployment has an author and a diff, and the entire history of "what was running when" is just the git log.',
