    deepDive: 'Two patterns dominate. Directory-per-environment keeps each environment in its own folder (envs/staging, envs/prod) on a single branch — the most popular approach because every environment\'s full state is visible at once and promotion is a clear file change in a PR. Branch-per-environment maps each environment to a branch and promotes by merging, which feels natural but makes drift between environments harder to see and is generally discouraged for that reason. Either way, promotion should move an immutable, already-tested artifact — the exact image digest that passed the lower environment — never rebuild for prod. Mature setups automate promotion: when staging goes green, a bot opens the production PR with the validated tag, preserving human approval while removing the manual copy-paste. The golden property is that the difference between staging and production is always visible as a Git diff.',
